-- mvtTileBBox: bounding box of the whole world at zoom 0
(-180,-85.05112877980659,180,85.05112877980659)
-- mvtTileBBoxMercator: bounding box of a tile in Web Mercator space
(0,0,2147483648,2147483648)
-- ST_TileEnvelope is an alias for mvtTileBBoxMercator
1
-- mvtTileBBox: a positive margin expands the box on every side
1	1	1	1
-- mvtTileBBox round-trips with mvtEncodeGeom: the tile centre projects to an interior pixel
(2048,2050)
-- mvtEncodeGeom: clip=true (the default) returns NULL for an out-of-tile point
1
-- mvtEncodeGeom: clip=false keeps an out-of-tile point (projected, not clipped)
1
-- mvtEncodeGeom: buffer 0 clips a point ~5px past the edge that buffer 16 keeps
1	1
-- mvtEncodeGeom: a polygon covering the whole tile is clipped to the tile box (buffer 0)
[[[(0,0),(0,4096),(4096,4096),(4096,0),(0,0)]]]
-- mvtEncodeGeom: a line crossing the tile edge is clipped to the buffer boundary
[[(1638,1850),(4096,1850)]]
-- mvtEncode: a geometry coordinate outside the representable MVT range is rejected
-- mvtEncode: a geometry delta exceeding the MVT command range is rejected (both vertices are in range)
-- tile indices must be < 2^zoom in mvtEncodeGeom, mvtTileBBox and mvtTileBBoxMercator
-- mvtEncodeGeom: fractional (non-integer) tile controls are rejected rather than silently truncated
-- the largest valid tile index for a zoom is accepted
1	1
